WHITE BURGUNDY

The white growths of 1950 yielded some remarkable wines. Unlike the red burgundies which were not of exceptional quality, many of the white burgundies were even superior to the 1949's, The listing below has been hand picked and represents the best year in each individual growth. Each wine can be laid down confidently . . . with the knowl- edge that when it is brought to the table, it is certain to please you and your guests.
